HEADWORD: laryngotracheotomy
<hw>la*ryn`go*tra`che*ot"o*my</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos>
<ety>[<ets>Larynx</ets> + <ets>tracheotomy</ets>.]</ety>
<fld>(Surg.)</fld> <def>The operation of cutting into the larynx and the
upper part of the trachea, -- a frequent operation for obstruction to
breathing.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

